info.description: Connect cities, grab ressources, and make sweet money from opponents piggybacking on your train/boat lines. All that on a terrible map projection of the Mediterranean.
info.helpText:
Moving things around:
• Every piece displays a shadow upon hovering over an intended valid slot on the main board or the players' scoring boards, so you know where to drop it.
• If you want to grab a city tile from the board, drag its top half, rather than the coordinates where its associated resource token is/was.
• Each stack of city tiles on your player board automatically rearranges to only display the highest tile (i.e. the one relevant to scoring).

Reading your scoring board:
• Each row of resource tokens will score the corresponding number of points at the bottom of the tableau. (Yes, a 1-size row scores 0 points.)
• Each column of resource tokens will score the corresponding number of points at the left of the tableau. (Yes, a 1-size column scores 0 points.)
• Your pile of gold is worth the highest number reached on the side of the pile. (Yes, 1 coin scores 0 points.)
